.TH "tsi721_cwrite_dma" 9 "tsi721_cwrite_dma" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tsi721_cwrite_dma \- Generate a RapidIO maintenance write transaction using Tsi721 BDMA engine
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tsi721_cwrite_dma
.BI "(struct rio_mport *mport "  ","
.BI "int index "  ","
.BI "u16 destid "  ","
.BI "u8 hopcount "  ","
.BI "u32 offset "  ","
.BI "int len "  ","
.BI "u32 data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mport" 12
RapidIO master port control structure
.IP "index" 12
ID of RapdiIO interface
.IP "destid" 12
Destination ID of transaction
.IP "hopcount" 12
Number of hops to target device
.IP "offset" 12
Offset into configuration space
.IP "len" 12
Length (in bytes) of the maintenance transaction
.IP "data" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Generates a RapidIO maintenance write transaction.
Returns 0 on success and -EINVAL or -EFAULT on failure.
